Inventory
Inventory related to regulated operations is valued at historical cost. Inventory related to nonregulated operations is valued at the lower of cost or market.
Inventory is charged to expense or capitalized to property, plant and equipment when issued, primarily using the average cost method. Excess or obsolete
inventory is written down to the lower of cost or net realizable value. Once inventory has been written down, it creates a new cost basis for the inventory
that is not subsequently written up. Provisions for inventory write-oﬀs were not material at December 31, 2022, and 2021, respectively. The components of
inventory are presented in the tables below.
