2023 North Carolina Rate Case
On January 19, 2023, Duke Energy Carolinas ﬁled a PBR application with the NCUC to request an increase in base rate retail revenues. The PBR Application
includes an MYRP to recover projected capital investments during the three year MYRP period. In addition to the MYRP, the PBR Application includes an
Earnings Sharing Mechanism, Residential Decoupling Mechanism and Performance Incentive Mechanisms as required by HB 951. If approved, the overall
retail revenue increase would be $501 million in Year 1, $172 million in Year 2 and $150 million in Year 3, for a combined total of $823 million or 15.7% by
early 2026. The rate increase is driven primarily by major transmission and distribution investments since the last rate case and projected in the MYRP, as
well as investments in energy storage and solar assets included in the MYRP consistent with the Carbon Plan. Duke Energy Carolinas plans to implement
temporary rates, subject to refund, on September 1, 2023, and has requested permanent rates be eﬀective by January 1, 2024. Duke Energy Carolinas
cannot predict the outcome of this matter.(a)
