Duke Energy and the Subsidiary Registrants ﬁle a consolidated federal income tax return and other state and jurisdictional returns. The Subsidiary
Registrants have a tax sharing agreement with Duke Energy for the allocation of consolidated tax liabilities and beneﬁts. Income taxes recorded represent
amounts the Subsidiary Registrants would incur as separate C-Corporations. The following table includes the balance of intercompany income tax receivables
and payables for the Subsidiary Registrants.
